{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddc40c938-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1761a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1761a"},"text":"§ 1761a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Officers of the board","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"At their first meeting after the annual meeting of the members, the directors shall elect from their number the board officers specified in the bylaws. Only one board officer may be compensated as an officer of the board and the bylaws shall specify such position as well as the specific duties of each of the board officers. The board shall elect from their number a financial officer who shall give adequate fidelity coverage in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1761b/2"},"text":"section 1761b(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddc40c939-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-26/ch750"},"text":"June 26, 1934, ch. 750","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 112, formerly § 13, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/354/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–354, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-09-22"},"text":"Sept. 22, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/632"},"text":"73 Stat. 632","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/150/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–150, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/270"},"text":"77 Stat. 270","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/206/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–206, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"